\cf2 /* here's the good stuff. this "index" variable makes it so that x percent of the time the impulse fires, the array will yield a new value. Each value in this array is the probability of that position in the array being chosen when the array is triggered. The output is the chosen position (or rather an index value). This index determines which pitches are used from the array further down in the FMsynth. In short, the probabilities in the "index" variable, correspond to the pitches that the synth will play. For example, for lots of Is and Vs I made positions one and five have higher probability values. (Note the array does not add up to 1, because I am normalizing the values (TWindex can do that for you if you do not want to worry about always adding up to 100%)). */\cf0 \
\
index = \cf3 TWindex\cf0 .kr(\cf3 CoinGate\cf0 .kr(prob,trig), 	[1,0.428,0.571,0.714,0.857,0.285,0.143,0.072,0.072],1);\
\
trigB = \cf3 Impulse\cf0 .kr(rateB, 0, \cf3 SinOsc\cf0 .kr(0.5,0,1,1));\
indexB = \cf3 TWindex\cf0 .kr(\cf3 CoinGate\cf0 .kr(probB,trigB), 	[1,0.428,0.571,0.714,0.857,0.285,0.143],1);\
